'''Graeme Hunter Kelling''' (4 April 1957 – 10 June 2004) was a guitarist with the Scottish [[pop music|pop]] band, [[Deacon Blue]].

He was born in [[Paisley]], Scotland, and educated at the [[High School of Glasgow]]. He died in 2004 in [[Glasgow]] at the age of 47, after a four-year battle with [[pancreatic cancer]].

