[[File:Portrait of John Edgerton 2nd Earl of Bridgewater.jpg|thumb|right|230px|The Earl of Bridgewater.]]
'''John Egerton, 2nd Earl of Bridgewater''' [[Privy Council of England|PC]] (30 May 1623 &ndash; 26 October 1686) was an [[England|English]] nobleman.

He was a son of [[John Egerton, 1st Earl of Bridgewater]] and his wife Lady Frances Stanley. His maternal grandparents were [[Ferdinando Stanley, 5th Earl of Derby]] and his wife Alice Spencer.

According to the [[Will of King Henry VIII]], his mother, at one time, was second-in-line to inherit England's throne.  However, Lady Frances Stanley's older sister, [[Anne Stanley, Countess of Castlehaven]], was passed over for King [[James VI of Scotland]].

He served as [[Lord Lieutenant of Buckinghamshire]] (1660&ndash;1686), [[Lord Lieutenant of Cheshire|Cheshire]] (1670&ndash;1676), [[Lord Lieutenant of Lancashire|Lancashire]] (1670&ndash;1676), and [[Hertfordshire]] (1681&ndash;1686), in addition to being invested as a [[Privy Council of the United Kingdom|Privy Council]]lor in 1679.  He was buried in [[Little Gaddesden]], [[Hertfordshire]].

In 1641 he married to [[Elizabeth Egerton|Elizabeth Cavendish]] (1626–1663), a daughter of [[William Cavendish, 1st Duke of Newcastle]] and his first wife Elizabeth Basset. They had four children:

*[[John Egerton, 3rd Earl of Bridgewater]] (9 November 1646 - 19 March 1701).
*William Egerton (born 15 August 1649). He married Honora Leigh.
*Thomas Egerton of [[Tatton Park]].
*Elizabeth Egerton (24 August 1653 - 1709). Married [[Robert Sidney, 4th Earl of Leicester]].

